---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Open Medical Skills — learn about our data collection practices, cookie usage, medical data handling, and HIPAA compliance stance."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
      Last updated: March 2, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-7">

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section>
        <p>
          Open Medical Skills is a project of <strong>IntelMedica.ai</strong>, a company founded by a physician.
          We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices. This Privacy
          Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding that data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 1. What We Collect -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1. What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>directory website</strong> — we catalog medical AI skills and plugins,
          but we do not currently require user accounts or collect personally identifiable information (PII).
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.1 Analytics Data (Anonymous)</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We may use privacy-focused web analytics (such as Plausible or similar) to understand how visitors use the site.
          This may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Page views and navigation paths</li>
          <li>Referral sources (where visitors came from)</li>
          <li>Device type and browser (aggregated, not user-specific)</li>
          <li>General geographic region (country-level only)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We <strong>do not</strong> use invasive tracking, cross-site cookies, or fingerprinting technologies.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.2 Theme Preference (Local Storage Only)</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Your dark mode / light mode preference is stored in your browser's <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-slate-800">localStorage</code>.
          This data never leaves your device and is not transmitted to our servers.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.3 GitHub Submissions</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          If you submit a skill or plugin via GitHub pull request or our web form, your submission will be publicly
          visible on GitHub. Your GitHub username and any information you include in the submission will be part of
          the public repository history.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Patient Data & PHI -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">2. Patient Data and Protected Health Information (PHI)</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>directory of tools</strong> — we do not collect, process, store, or transmit
          any patient data or Protected Health Information (PHI). We are <strong>not a covered entity</strong> under HIPAA.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Each listed skill is an independent third-party project with its own data handling practices.
          <strong>You are responsible for reviewing the privacy policy, data handling practices, and compliance posture
          of any skill or plugin before deploying it in a clinical, research, or production environment.</strong>
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Cookies -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">3. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We use minimal cookies or similar technologies:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li><strong>Essential cookies</strong>: None currently required for site functionality</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies</strong>: Only if privacy-focused analytics are enabled (anonymous, no PII)</li>
          <li><strong>Third-party cookies</strong>: We do not embed third-party trackers, ad networks, or social media pixels</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          You can disable cookies in your browser settings. Disabling cookies will not affect your ability to browse the directory.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Third-Party Services -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We rely on the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>GitHub</strong>: Skill submissions, pull requests, and issue tracking are hosted on GitHub.
            GitHub's privacy policy applies to any data you submit via GitHub.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Pages (or similar)</strong>: Our website is hosted on a content delivery network (CDN)
            for performance and security. The CDN provider may log basic request metadata (IP addresses, timestamps)
            for security and DDoS protection purposes.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Medical Disclaimer -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">5. Medical Disclaimer</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 dark:border-amber-800/50 dark:bg-amber-950/30">
          <p class="font-medium text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">Important Medical Disclaimer</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
            Open Medical Skills is a <strong>directory of tools</strong> — it does not provide medical advice,
            diagnosis, or treatment. The skills listed here are third-party software tools intended to assist
            healthcare professionals. They are <strong>not medical devices</strong> (unless explicitly stated and
            FDA-cleared) and do not replace clinical judgment, medical training, or the physician-patient relationship.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. HIPAA Disclaimer -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">6. HIPAA Compliance Stance</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>publicly accessible directory website</strong>. We are not a covered entity
          or business associate under the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). We do not handle
          PHI or enter into Business Associate Agreements (BAAs).
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you deploy a skill from this directory in a HIPAA-regulated environment, you are responsible for ensuring
          that the skill's author has appropriate compliance measures in place and that you execute any necessary BAAs
          with the skill provider.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 7. Data Retention -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">7. Data Retention</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Because we do not collect personal data (beyond anonymous analytics), there is no personal data to retain or delete.
          If we introduce user accounts or personalized features in the future, we will update this policy accordingly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 8. Your Rights -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">8. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Depending on your location, you may have rights under data protection laws such as GDPR (Europe), CCPA (California),
          or similar regulations. Because we do not collect PII, these rights are largely not applicable to our current operations.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you have questions about your privacy rights or wish to exercise them, contact us at the address below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 9. Children's Privacy -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">9. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is not directed at children under the age of 13 (or 16 in the EU). We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has submitted information to us, please
          contact us immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 10. International Users -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">10. International Users</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is accessible worldwide. If you access the site from outside the United States, you
          acknowledge that any data you submit (e.g., via GitHub) may be processed and stored in the United States
          or other jurisdictions where our service providers operate.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 11. Changes to This Policy -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">11. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements.
          Updates will be posted on this page with a new "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the site after
          changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 12. Contact -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">12. Contact Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900/50">
          <p class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">IntelMedica.ai</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@intelmedica.ai" class="text-primary hover:underline">privacy@intelmedica.ai</a></p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400">
            (Contact details will be updated with full mailing address and phone number when available)
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer Note -->
      <section class="mt-12 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8 dark:border-slate-800">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500">
          <strong>Open Medical Skills</strong> is a project of <strong>IntelMedica.ai</strong>, founded by a physician.
          We are committed to transparency, privacy, and building tools that serve the healthcare community responsibly.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
